Find partition to mount
    > lsblk
    or
    > sudo fdisk -l
    - will be /dev/sdXX - eg. /dev/sdc1

Find UUID for that partition
    > blkid

Create a mount point
    > sudo mkdir /data
    - create a user group called data
    > sudo groupadd data
    - add your user to that group
    > sudo usermod -aG data david
    - change ownership of mount point to add that group
    > sudo chown -R :data /data

Add automount entry
    > sudo nano /etc/fstab
    - add entry for example:
    UUID=14D82C19D82BF81E /data    auto nosuid,nodev,nofail,x-gvfs-show 0 0

Test if it works
    > sudo mount -a
